intro: Cyathodes disticha, commonly known as the two-branched cyathodes, is a flowering plant native to certain regions of Southeast Asia. It belongs to the family Euphorbiaceae, which includes many species with unique floral structures. The plant is characterized by its compact, branched inflorescence known as a cyathode, which is typical of the Euphorbiaceae family. Its small, inconspicuous flowers are often surrounded by modified leaves called cyathophylls. The plant is typically found in tropical and subtropical environments, growing in moist, shaded habitats.
